st add a `/monitor` command to the `agent_wrapper.py` that keeps the wrapper process running and starts the monitor thread, in accordance with the user's instructions. Then, I'll need to check the integration with `trading_bot.py`.\n\n\n"},{"type":"text","text":"I will read `src/trading_bot.py` to understand its relationship with `src/agent_wrapper.py`.\n\n"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"read_1771158040116_631","name":"read","arguments":{"file_path":"src/trading_bot.py"},"thoughtSignature":""}],"api":"google-vertex","provider":"google-vertex","model":"gemini-3-pro-preview","usage":{"input":9459,"output":1159,"cacheRead":5788,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":10618,"cost":{"input":0.018918,"output":0.013908,"cacheRead":0.0011576000000000002,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0.0339836}},"stopReason":"toolUse","timestamp":1771158026260}}
